### Describe the bug

I'm not sure if this is a bug or intentional, but the `@PostConstruct` and `@PreDestroy` annotated methods are never working.

```
@ApplicationScoped
public class Test {

    @PostConstruct
    public void test() {
        System.out.println("construct");
    }

    @PreDestroy
    public void test2() {
        System.out.println("destroy");
    }
}

```

If this is for some reason intentional, how to get it working?

